Vheadline
p2
VPaying tribute to Thyagaraja
p3
sVnews
p4
VThe College of Fine Arts and Media Education is a new wing of Andhra Mahila Sabha that came up three years ago with an ambition to serve the field of classical arts and is now affiliated to Telugu University.The college held &#8216;Thyagaraja Aradhana&#8217; for the first time attended by a host of leading Carnatic musicians.   Vocalist and scholar K.S.R. Balakrishna Sastry introduced thePancharatna Kirtanasof Thyagaraja depicting their significance.The ensemble included 40 members rendering thekirtanaswith one voice.On the following day Sangeetha Ksheerasagaram organised &#8216;Thyagaraja Pancharatna Kirtana Goshti Ganam&#8217; at Thyagaraya Ganasabha&#8217;s mini hall, with Komanduri Seshadri leading the chorus and narrating the features of each of thekirtanas.Tadepalli Lokanadha Sarma, Shyam Sundar, Jayalakshmi, Vardhani, Bhagyalakshmi, P.V. Subba Rao and many artistes took part in this.
